<br>
For the first 6 AA, I recommend Run Speed 3 and Innate Charm 3. Innate Metabolism is for people with too many AA, I think.<br>
<br>
FYI, SCM3 effectively increases your mana pool by 20%.<br>
<br>
With PoP, your maximum Int is 355, at level 65 plus appropriate AAs. This is 255 + (5 levels x 5 Int/level) + (5 steps x 5 Int/Step for Plana Power) + (5 steps x 10 Int/Step for Innate Enlightenment).<br>
<br>
I'm a 65 cleric, and I regularly duo with a 65 chanter having 350+ AA. Our favorite spot is in Plane of Fire south of zone-in. He tashes then charms a big spider (having 30-35k HP). My job is to heal the spider (to reduce time spent recharming), and to keep the chanter alive during recharms (such as by rooting the to-be-killed mob, and healing or DivArbing the chanter as he runs past). We've gotten to be a pretty good team, and earn one AA per 90 minutes or so. <p><a href="mailto:dforthof@adobe.com">Forthoffer,</a>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=148568">65 cleric,</a>
<a href="http://www.theshadoworder.com/">The Shadow Order,</a>
<a href="http://pub130.ezboard.com/beqasylum">Lanys T'Vyl</a>
