Well its been about 3 months since I wrote this guide.  I reread it today and the commentary to it and wanted add some thoughts.<br>
<br>
First off is commentary about mezz.   It is still the best crowd control method available.  There are mobs in the planes that are not rootable and mezzing is #1.  This does not downplay the fact that Root is more likely to stick on a first application.  Root - Tash - Mezz - Slow might be the way to do effectively control an add.  The Crypt of Decay and the Plane of Tactics require effective Crowd Control.  They are places where a Shaman is not necessarily an effective substitute to a Chanter.  Finally for those just hitting the non-stun phase of life, remember Mezz is a great way to break a mobs spell casting...particularly for gating mobs (like the Scourge Hobogoblin in PoN).<br>
<br>
People have been spending a lot of time with AA.  The Defensive AAs of Lightning Reflexes 5 and Inate Defense 5 seem to work very well.  These are higher priority than they used to be.  I have Eldritch Rune 3 and have to say, that it is a lifesaver.  Its instant and can be used on the run.  I highly recommend it.  I also have Animation Empathy 3.  I prefer the 62 pet with SoV and NDT to a DC pet anyday.  Most groups have not run into a Chanter with AE3, but I believe its much more versatile than DC and the pet has higher DPS (imho).  He does not hit as hard, but hits very fast and procs like MAD with NDT.  That pet can solo slowed mobs below 50 without any healing.  Above 50, Uproar works pretty well (I soloed the guy who drops Soulstripper and that Mage Cloak several times in this config - also soloed US in Velks and all the nameds there that way).  I have not tried too many mobs above 55 soloing with the animation.  The view of Total Domination has gotten more negative over time.  I have put it near the end of the queue of things I want to get.<br>
<br>
Ornate Silk is now getting to be relatively common in the bazaar.  Pretty pricey still but there are 2 pieces of special mention.  The Bracelet (FT2) and the Pants (C4) are the best items of the bunch.  I am basically equipped with SS armor and the rest are small upgrades (and very expensive if purchased) to what I have.<br>
<br>
Spell Research has gotten to be a reasonable money maker.  Its possible to scan the bazaar periodically and find rareish pages at moderate prices.  The prices on the upper-50s - 60 rare drop spells is generally higher than anything short of level 65 spells (like Topor).  One should be able to pick up enough materials to get research leveled to 184 (49 spell trivial I believe) at a pretty modest price.<br>
<br>
Finally, I am really looking forward to LDoN.  Getting back to dungeon crawls will bring forward the Enchanter as the Premier Battle Management class going.  Some of my friends and I did the new Droga the other day.  The mob at the entry ran on us in a very strange way (up - not down) and we got lot of adds.  There were so many adds that I could not keep them all mezzed, they broke before I could get back to them.  But our MA went defensive and we all ran (and lived).  What fun to be mezzing like mad again (we had a 2 group setup in CT the other day in 4C pyramid and 2 of us managed a 14 mob pull - he he).<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Coercer of Vazelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#330000>- </font><a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm>Eq Enchanters Realm</a><font color=#330000> - </font><a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs>FAQs</a> <font color=#330000> - </font><a href="http://www.geocities.com/eqenchantersrealm/">Eq Enchanters Realm Main Page</a><font color=#330000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.245d<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

